HRSA Public Health Nursing Grants content skip header and navigation H R S A News Brief http www hhs gov U S Department of Health Human Services Health Resources and Services Administration HRSA NEWS ROOM http newsroom hrsa gov http newsroom hrsa gov May 21 2003 Contact HRSA Press Office 301 443 3376 HRSA Grants Support Public Health Nursing Field Experiences HHS Health Resources and Services Administration has announced grants totaling 249 848 to 10 schools of nursing to strengthen the field experience component of public health nursing baccalaureate programs The awards will provide seed money to plan implement and evaluate public health nursing field experiences including the preparation of faculty and health department staff Nursing students will learn about core functions of public health essential public health services the missions of state and local health departments and how public health practitioners work together to protect the public s health HRSA s Division of Nursing funds a wide range of grant programs that strengthen existing nursing programs and seek to reduce the nation s critical nursing shortage Recently six new programs were authorized under the Nurse Reinvestment Act of 2002 to increase the number of qualified nurses and the quality of nursing services across the nation Nursing Scholarships Building Career Ladders Internship and Residency Enhancing Patient Care Nurse Retention Comprehensive Geriatric Education and Nurse Faculty Loans For more information visit http bhpr hrsa gov nursing reinvestmentact htm http bhpr hrsa gov nursing reinvestmentact htm A list of grant awards which are effective July 1 2003 is attached below For more information contact Irene Sandvold at 301 443 6333 or mailto isandvold hrsa gov isandvold hrsa gov Public Health Nursing Field Experiences Grant Awards Organization City State Amount Georgetown University Washington D C 24 991 University of Miami Coral Gables Fla 25 000 Medical College of Georgia Augusta Ga 25 000 U